From d09f7cbf695147e5f2cb2b691f2643512a454af5 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Jianhui Zhao <zhaojh329@gmail.com>
Date: Tue, 31 Mar 2026 17:40:58 +0800
Subject: [PATCH 1/2] fix(ubus): unregister subscriber when subscribe fails

Rollback the local subscriber registration if ubus_subscribe() fails.

lua_ubus_subscribe() registers a local ubus subscriber object before
subscribing it to the target object. When the target disappears in that
window, ubus_subscribe() can fail after the subscriber has already been
inserted into libubus's local object tree. Without cleanup, this leaves
a stale registered subscriber behind and repeated retries can eventually
corrupt the object tree and crash in avl_insert().

Signed-off-by: Jianhui Zhao <zhaojh329@gmail.com>
---
 ubus.c | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/ubus.c b/ubus.c
index 78390e2..c9048d0 100644
--- a/ubus.c
+++ b/ubus.c
@@ -759,6 +759,7 @@ static int lua_ubus_subscribe(lua_State *L)
 
     ret = ubus_subscribe(&ctx->ctx, sub, id);
     if (ret) {
+        ubus_unregister_subscriber(&ctx->ctx, sub);
         lua_pushnil(L);
         lua_pushstring(L, ubus_strerror(ret));
         return 2;
-- 
